Trading Update Summary - Change Financial Limited (ASX: CCA)

Key Highlights:

  • FY25 (Unaudited) Results:
  • Revenue: US$15.1m (A$23.2m) – up 42% YoY (exceeding guidance of >30% growth).
  • Maiden positive Underlying EBITDA (exact figure to be confirmed in audited results).

  • Net cash flow positive in Q4 FY25 due to higher client invoicing and cost reductions.

  • FY26 Guidance:

  • Revenue: US$16.5m – US$18.0m (A$25.4m – A$27.7m).
  • Underlying EBITDA: US$2.5m – US$3.5m (A$3.8m – A$5.4m) – significant margin improvement.

  • Expected to be net cash flow positive for full year FY26.

  • Long-term Growth:

  • 3-year revenue CAGR (FY23-FY25): 22% (expected to rise to 25% based on FY26 midpoint).
  • Target: Maintain >20% revenue CAGR medium-to-long term.

No capital raising, M&A, or material corporate actions identified.

Key Material Information:

  • Extended Reconnaissance Programme: 24-hole hand auger drill programme initiated at Central Rutile Project to assess potential mineralisation continuity from Peak Minerals' adjacent Afanloum licence.
  • Geological Upside: DY6 anticipates similar high-grade rutile mineralisation on its Nsimbo and Alamba licences, given shared geological units with Peak Minerals' discovery (e.g., 7m @ 5.1% HM).
  • Recent Expansion: Central Rutile Project enlarged to 4,974km² (from 2,140km²) via Weaver licences acquisition (8 July 2025).

Rationale: Focused on near-term exploration catalysts and project scalability, with immediate drilling targeting potential resource extension. Excluded operational/non-impactful details.

• First U.S. revenue: US$0.6M five-year contract signed with Tanner Health for Salix® Coronary Anatomy platform, expected in current quarter.
  • Future revenue potential: Pathway for additional revenue from Salix® Coronary Plaque and Coronary Flow modules post-FDA clearances.
  • Commercial integration: Salix® to be rolled out across Tanner Health’s network (five hospitals, cardiovascular centers, and 30 physician practices).
  • Market expansion: Active discussions with other U.S. hospital networks and preparation for FDA clearance of Salix® Coronary Plaque module.

No capital raising, trading halt, or financials disclosed.

• Tendering process commenced for Caravel Copper Project process plant design and key infrastructure, awards expected from August 2025.
  • Final metallurgy studies simplified the 30Mtpa plant design, improving project economics.
  • Ore Reserve: 1.4Mt contained copper; target production: ~65,000tpa copper, 900tpa molybdenum.
  • $15M loan facility secured from Regal Funds Management (previously announced).
  • Study Manager appointed to oversee tendering and Definitive Feasibility Study (DFS) preparation.

No material trading or capital-raising information identified.

• Achievement: Demonstrated cryogenic operation of TMR sensors for quantum computing applications.
  • Potential Applications: Platform-agnostic use across superconducting, spin-based, and hybrid quantum systems; potential for magnetic noise monitoring and advanced sensing markets.
  • Commercial Opportunities: Actively pursuing partnerships for bespoke sensor applications in quantum, aerospace, and defence.

No capital, financial, or trading-impacting details identified.

Summary of Material Information:

  • Key Findings:
    • Acquisition of 36 km² new tenure in Southern Sweden, expanding total landholding to 159 km².
    • Initial rock sampling identified IOCG-style mineralization at two high-priority prospects:
    • Domstugan: 0.8% Cu, 1.2 g/t Au, 48 g/t Ag.
    • Tintorp: 2.2% Cu, 0.3 g/t Au, 0.07% Mo.
    • Confirmed district-scale potential with three additional copper-bearing occurrences.
  • Next Steps:
    • Prioritize follow-up at Domstugan and Tintorp.
    • Advance drill target definition and geophysical surveys.

Rationale: Highlights focus on materially significant exploration results, expansion of tenure, and high-grade assays that could impact valuation and future capital raises. Non-operational details (e.g., historical context, director quotes) excluded.

Material Information Summary

Exploration Results Announcement

  • Discovery: New large-scale gold target identified at La Brea, ~15km north of the existing 1.5Moz Ternera Gold Deposit (El Zorro Project, Chile).
  • High-Grade Assays:
  • Multiple high-grade surface samples, including:
    • 1.00m @ 22.10 g/t Au (EZTR005000)
    • 1.00m @ 11.80 g/t Au (EZTR005065)
    • 4.00m @ 4.85 g/t Au (EZTR005259)
  • 40% of samples returned gold grades >0.10 g/t Au, indicating widespread mineralization.
  • Scale: Four mineralized trends up to 200m wide and 4km long.
  • Next Steps:
  • Trenching program to refine drill targets.
  • Maiden drilling planned in coming months.

Key Implications for Valuation/Liquidity:

  1. Potential for new gold system with similarities to Ternera Deposit.
  2. High-grade surface results suggest further upside if confirmed by drilling.

No capital raising, financials, or material corporate updates identified.

Material Information Summary (G50 Corp Limited – ASX: G50 | 10 July 2025)

Key Highlights (Exploration Results – Golconda Project, Arizona)

  • New Discovery Confirmed:
  • 47.2m @ 2.00 g/t Au, 40.2 g/t Ag, 0.29% Zn (GRC22), including 16.8m @ 5.19 g/t Au, 100.2 g/t Ag.
  • 77.7m @ 0.76 g/t Au, 11 g/t Ag (GRC21), with 7.6m @ 5.5 g/t Au, 32.4 g/t Ag.
  • 97.5m @ 0.27 g/t Au, 4.8 g/t Ag, 0.7% Zn (GRC17), ending in mineralization.
  • Gallium Potential:
  • Significant intercepts: 216m @ 18.4 g/t Ga (GRC13), 209m @ 17.7 g/t Ga (GRC14).
  • Confirmed in alteration zones (muscovite/kaolinite/k-feldspar); potential for strategic mineral extraction.
  • Next Steps:
  • Assays pending for remaining holes (GRC27–38) – expected in 4–6 weeks.
  • Planning underway for follow-up drilling to test depth/extensions.

Operational Context

  • Drilling Focus: 700m strike length of Tub Zone (gold-silver-zinc veins).
  • Mineralization Open: Along strike and at depth; no true width estimated yet.
  • Jurisdiction: Arizona (mining-friendly, near established projects like Mineral Park).

No capital raising, financials, or corporate actions announced.

Material Information Summary

Exploration Update

  • Lucy Creek 2 Prospect (Manganese & Base Metals):
  • High-grade manganese detected via portable XRF (e.g., 33.56% MnO in sample RCLCK001).
  • Elevated base metals: Pb (up to 1,131 ppm), Zn (up to 1,133 ppm), Ag (up to 30 ppm).
  • Mineralisation style suggests hydrothermal potential, analogous to Bootu Creek (historic resource: 32.5Mt @ 22.6% Mn).

  • Planned work:

    • Airborne magnetic/radiometric survey (partially NT Gov-funded).
    • Ground EM for targeting conductive zones.

  • Bomb Diggity Prospect (Au-Bi-Cu-Zn):

  • Follow-up on 15m @ 0.45 g/t Au, 0.17% Bi, 0.35% Cu (from prior drilling).
  • Planned deep diamond drillhole (partially funded by NTGS grant).

Key Upcoming Catalysts

  • Geophysical surveys to refine drill targets at both prospects.

Material Information Summary (Corporate Presentation - ASX:GLA)

Investment Highlights

  • Uranium Exploration Focus: Targeting sandstone-hosted uranium deposits in Tanzania’s Selous Basin (Karoo Supergroup).
  • Key Project (Mkuju):
  • Contains Likuyu North deposit (JORC MRE: 4.6Mlb U₃O₈ at 267ppm, 100ppm cut-off).
  • ISR potential: Study confirms suitability for low-cost in-situ recovery (ISR) mining.
  • Mtonya-SWC corridor: High-grade intersections (e.g., 3.8m @ 2,458ppm eU₃O₈ at SWC).
  • Foxy Project: Untested uranium mineralization (2008 drill results: 6m @ 213ppm U₃O₈).
  • Eland Project: Early-stage Nb-Ta-U syenite target (44m @ 174ppm U₃O₈, 953ppm Nb₂O₅ via channel sampling).

Exploration Strategy

  • Prioritize Likuyu North expansion and Mtonya-SWC roll-front targets.
  • Planned low-cost drilling to test high-priority zones (e.g., SWC "nose" target, Likuyu South redox front).

Risks/Catalysts

  • Foreign estimates (Mtonya): Non-JORC inferred resource of 1.9Mlb U₃O₈ (293ppm, 100ppm cut-off) – requires further validation.
  • Uranium price leverage: Presentation highlights rising uranium market (spot price >USD70/lb).

No material financials or capital-raising details disclosed.

Material Information Summary (ASX: WCN – Diamond Drilling Commences at Rae Copper Project)

  • Exploration Update:
  • Diamond drilling has commenced at the Hulk sedimentary target (100% owned by WCN), focused on a large untested geophysical anomaly.
  • Three initial drill holes target distinct zones:
    • HLK25001: Eastern margin near historic intercept (29m at 0.57% Cu).

  • RC drilling to resume at Danvers prospect, where prior results included high-grade intercepts (e.g., 175m at 2.5% Cu & 8.66g/t Ag).

  • Drone MT survey underway to refine targeting at Danvers.
